  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Values-Based Community Livestock Development Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will support an extensive community livestock development project covering 6 districts and reaching 13,500 families. It will provide 4,500 families with a total of 13,500 goats and 450 breeding bucks. Participants will pass on the gift to an additional 9,000 families. Families will also receive fodder saplings and grass and vegetable seeds and will build 225 bio-gas plants, 2,200 smokeless stoves and 900 hygienic toilets. Training will cover Heifer&#x2019;s Cornerstones, group management, animal handling, gender equity and vegetable farming. The project will also incorporate the values-based literacy program and train 34 village animal health workers. Heifer Nepal will also identify and train 25 local partners to help implement the project.</narrative>
  </description>
